Rating: 3
Tasty, easy recipe that you can tweak to your own taste. It's clear from the prior 25 reviews that everyone has their own ideas about whether there should be less butter, more butter, more cheese, more liquids, less liquids, more sage, other spices, etc. That's fine - mashed potatoes is one of those staples that we have personal preferences about! Here was my tweak: I threw sage sprigs in the boiling water as well as soaking sage leaves in the milk, and the taste of the potatoes was great. Just be sure you add plenty of salt and pepper to the potatoes as you mash them; this brings out the sage and goat cheese flavors.

