We made this several times this past fall and winter as we enjoy the flavor profile. Two comments 1.) First steeping sage in the milk for a period of time pronounces the flavor. Or you may add sage to the boiling water. 2.) For added aesthetic appeal, I suggest adding red and blue sage flowers as a garnish just prior serving. (The edible flowers are from pineapple and blue anise sage, respectively.) Enjoy

